      <section eId="sec_CCP-4551">
        <num>CCP 4551</num>
        <heading>4551.  Judgment</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the judgment of interdiction, the court shall:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Appoint a curator.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Appoint an undercurator, unless an undercurator is not required by law.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>State that the powers of the curator commence only upon qualification.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Direct the clerk of court to record the judgment in the conveyance and mortgage
records of the parish where it was rendered.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CCP-4551__subsec_A__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Set forth the name, domicile, age, and current address of the defendant.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4551__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In addition, a judgment of limited interdiction shall confer upon the limited
curator only those powers necessitated by the interests of the limited interdict to be protected
through limited interdiction and shall state that the limited interdict retains the capacity of
a natural person except as expressly limited by the judgment.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4551__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In addition, a judgment granting or extending temporary or preliminary
interdiction shall set forth the date of termination.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112012</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
